ealth advocacy after he suffered from depression and suicidal ideation, the NBA player Kevin Love'sopen letterabout his struggle with panic attacks and anxiety.\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3391050696975487e-57, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}, {\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999999997644409, \"rank\": 1.4775375332953244e-10, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1131, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Love\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8328609066990157e-23, \"text\": \"Kevin Love\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Love\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Love\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Discussions\", \"from\": 725, \"to\": 736}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 756}, {\"ngram\": \"the cost\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 769}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive life\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 851}, {\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most successful athletes\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"Osaka'sboundary\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"-enforcing refusal\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 962}, {\"ngram\": \"press conferences\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 990}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Open\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1009}, {\"ngram\": \"depression\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"suicidal ideation\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"his struggle\", \"from\": 1160, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"panic attacks\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"anxiety\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each of these athletes has their particular struggle, but the idea that achieving the highest sporting honors cannot salve the pressures of elite athletic life is well established.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1388, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these athletes\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1230}, {\"ngram\": \"their particular struggle\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1274}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest sporting honors\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1317}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressures\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"elite athletic life\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Studies have shown, for instance, that silver medalists focus more than athletes awarded the bronze medal on what pushing just a little harder might have yielded-what they missed out on rather than what they achieved.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1606, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Studies\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1421}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medalists\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1444}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1461, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal\", \"from\": 1478, \"to\": 1494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Depression associated with the pressure of competition can shape an athlete's career and their life after sports, even for gold medalists and the all-time-greatest competitors; it has become widespread enough that athletes trying to raise awareness have called depression anepidemicamong Olympians.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Depression\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1617}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete's career\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1691}, {\"ngram\": \"their life\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1706}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medalists\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1744}, {\"ngram\": \"the all-time-greatest competitors\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1782}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1855}, {\"ngram\": \"depression anepidemicamong Olympians\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1904}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An elite athlete's life is necessarily dominated by training and an almost delusional fixation on doing more, being more, than any other competitor.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"An elite athlete's life\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1969}, {\"ngram\": \"an almost delusional fixation\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2003}, {\"ngram\": \"any other competitor\", \"from\": 2036, \"to\": 2056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of their mind must be given over to analyzing their performance, visualizing improvement, and steeling themselves through the work to get there.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2207, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their mind\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2076}, {\"ngram\": \"their performance\", \"from\": 2109, \"to\": 2126}, {\"ngram\": \"improvement\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2151}, {\"ngram\": \"the work\", \"from\": 2185, \"to\": 2193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But some experts are finding that loosening this unwavering commitment may actually help athletes ease into life beyond those highs-and perhaps even become better athletes.\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2380, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some experts\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2224}, {\"ngram\": \"this unwavering commitment\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2278}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2305}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"those highs\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2339}, {\"ngram\": \"better athletes\", \"from\": 2364, \"to\": 2379}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David Lavallee, a professor who studies well-being and sports at Abertay University, in the U.K., told me that the greater a person's \\\"athlete identity\\\"-that is, the more their persona is enmeshed with their role as an athlete-the higher the chance that their mental health could deteriorate in times of adversity, not to mention when they transition out of sports.\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2449, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abertay_University\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Abertay University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abertay_University\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abertay_University\"}, {\"begin\": 2476, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9622034389435598, \"rank\": 0.039281257364248104, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"David Lavallee\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"a professor\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2411}, {\"ngram\": \"well-being\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2445}, {\"ngram\": \"a person's \\\"athlete\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2526}, {\"ngram\": \"identity\\\"-that\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2541}, {\"ngram\": \"their persona\", \"from\": 2555, \"to\": 2568}, {\"ngram\": \"their role\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2610}, {\"ngram\": \"the higher the chance\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2632}, {\"ngram\": \"their mental health\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2657}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"adversity\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2697}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Self-identity can be quite malleable, but \\\"when that constant pressure to be one thing is there, it's very hard to find balance,\\\" he told me.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Self-identity\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2763}, {\"ngram\": \"that constant pressure\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2820}, {\"ngram\": \"one thing\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2836}, {\"ngram\": \"balance\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2877}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the research on silver medalists hints, for some athletes, the pressure to win is so great that anything less can be an indictment of their sense of self.\", \"from\": 2892, \"to\": 3049, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the research\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2907}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medalists hints\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2952}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 2954, \"to\": 2966}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"an indictment\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3025}, {\"ngram\": \"their sense\", \"from\": 3029, \"to\": 3040}, {\"ngram\": \"self\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 10-time Olympic medalist Allison Schmitt-one of the most successfulU.S.\", \"from\": 3053, \"to\": 3128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3082, \"end\": 3089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Engine_Company\", \"score\": 0.7748725263536637, \"rank\": 0.1568293571103538, \"text\": \"Allison\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Engine_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allison_Engine_Company\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most successfulU.S.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"swimmers of all time-experienced this type of challenge firsthand.\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3195, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3137}, {\"ngram\": \"all time-experienced this type\", \"from\": 3141, \"to\": 3171}, {\"ngram\": \"challenge\", \"from\": 3175, \"to\": 3184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She described herself to me as \\\"a quirky type of person\\\" who is fun-loving and generally upbeat.\", \"from\": 3196, \"to\": 3292, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a quirky type\", \"from\": 3228, \"to\": 3241}, {\"ngram\": \"person\", \"from\": 3245, \"to\": 3251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She remembers thinking, after winning silver in her first individual event at the 2012 London Games:I am supposed to be happy.\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 3331, \"to\": 3337}, {\"ngram\": \"her first individual event\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3367}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2012 London Games\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3392}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is supposed to be great.\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3449, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I had a smile on my face-I just got silver at the Olympics,\\\" she told me.\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a smile\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3463}, {\"ngram\": \"my face\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 3486, \"to\": 3492}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3496, \"to\": 3508}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it was still almost like a failure.\\\"\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a failure\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3563}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps, a close friend and a training mate, helped her reframe her approach in the moment.\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3569, \"end\": 3575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.973529572118372e-14, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a close friend\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3591}, {\"ngram\": \"a training mate\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3611}, {\"ngram\": \"her approach\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3644}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Michael hit me in the legs and was like,You have the strongest legs in the competition!\\\"\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3749, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Michael\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3668}, {\"ngram\": \"the legs\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3687}, {\"ngram\": \"the strongest legs\", \"from\": 3710, \"to\": 3728}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 3732, \"to\": 3747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"she recalled.\", \"from\": 3750, \"to\": 3763, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was like,Oh, I do?\", \"from\": 3764, \"to\": 3785, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone else believes in me?That was a huge turning point.\\\"\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3845, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Someone\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3793}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge turning point\", \"from\": 3823, \"to\": 3843}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She went on to win three gold medals at that Olympics.\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3900, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three gold medals\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 3882}, {\"ngram\": \"that Olympics\", \"from\": 3886, \"to\": 3899}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after the highs of London, the comedown, mixed with the pressure to continue performing at that level, began to consume her.\", \"from\": 3901, \"to\": 4029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3924, \"end\": 3930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.1862796219585317e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the highs\", \"from\": 3911, \"to\": 3920}, {\"ngram\": \"the comedown\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3944}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 3969}, {\"ngram\": \"that level\", \"from\": 3996, \"to\": 4006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She failed to make the team for the 2013 World Championships; later, she was diagnosed with depression, and has since spent her career in and out of the pool advocating for athlete mental health.\", \"from\": 4030, \"to\": 4225, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4057}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2013 World Championships\", \"from\": 4062, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"depression\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4132}, {\"ngram\": \"her career\", \"from\": 4154, \"to\": 4164}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 4179, \"to\": 4187}, {\"ngram\": \"athlete mental health\", \"from\": 4203, \"to\": 4224}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The traditional outlook on sports holds that a narrow focus on athletic achievement is essentially the price of admission.\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4351, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The traditional outlook\", \"from\": 4229, \"to\": 4252}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 4256, \"to\": 4262}, {\"ngram\": \"a narrow focus\", \"from\": 4274, \"to\": 4288}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic achievement\", \"from\": 4292, \"to\": 4312}, {\"ngram\": \"the price\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4337}, {\"ngram\": \"admission\", \"from\": 4341, \"to\": 4350}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But leaving more room for other parts of life has advantages.One paper, published inPsychology of Sport and Exercise, found that Olympic athletes who juggled dual careers while competing reported feeling less limited when they retired.\", \"from\": 4352, \"to\": 4587, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more room\", \"from\": 4364, \"to\": 4373}, {\"ngram\": \"other parts\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4389}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 4393, \"to\": 4397}, {\"ngram\": \"advantages\", \"from\": 4402, \"to\": 4412}, {\"ngram\": \"One paper\", \"from\": 4413, \"to\": 4422}, {\"ngram\": \"inPsychology\", \"from\": 4434, \"to\": 4446}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4455}, {\"ngram\": \"Exercise\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4468}, {\"ngram\": \"dual careers\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4522}, {\"ngram\": \"reported feeling\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also felt more in control of their life decisions-which researchers found to be a major factor in success beyond the field of play.\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4724, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"control\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4618}, {\"ngram\": \"their life decisions\", \"from\": 4622, \"to\": 4642}, {\"ngram\": \"researchers\", \"from\": 4649, \"to\": 4660}, {\"ngram\": \"a major factor\", \"from\": 4673, \"to\": 4687}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 4691, \"to\": 4698}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 4706, \"to\": 4715}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 4719, \"to\": 4723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This kind of multitasking does not necessarily mean compromising athletic performance.\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4811, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This kind\", \"from\": 4725, \"to\": 4734}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic performance\", \"from\": 4790, \"to\": 4810}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few years ago, Lavallee was asked by the National Rugby League, in Australia, to analyze the correlation between rugby players' performance and their engagement in activities that would prep them for life after the sport, such as school and work.\", \"from\": 4812, \"to\": 5060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4855, \"end\": 4876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999100191457, \"rank\": 8.998110973112754e-08, \"text\": \"National Rugby League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q10962\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rugby_League\"}, {\"begin\": 4881, \"end\": 4890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.9999935463228189, \"rank\": 4.7932643885932715e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lavallee\", \"from\": 4829, \"to\": 4837}, {\"ngram\": \"the correlation\", \"from\": 4903, \"to\": 4918}, {\"ngram\": \"rugby players' performance\", \"from\": 4927, \"to\": 4953}, {\"ngram\": \"their engagement\", \"from\": 4958, \"to\": 4974}, {\"ngram\": \"activities\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4988}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 5014, \"to\": 5018}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 5025, \"to\": 5034}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 5044, \"to\": 5050}, {\"ngram\": \"work\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The results surprised even Lavallee: The most single-minded players performed less well over the three-year course of the study than the players with outside interests.\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The results\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5072}, {\"ngram\": \"even Lavallee\", \"from\": 5083, \"to\": 5096}, {\"ngram\": \"The most single-minded players\", \"from\": 5098, \"to\": 5128}, {\"ngram\": \"the three-year course\", \"from\": 5154, \"to\": 5175}, {\"ngram\": \"the study\", \"from\": 5179, \"to\": 5188}, {\"ngram\": \"the players\", \"from\": 5194, \"to\": 5205}, {\"ngram\": \"outside interests\", \"from\": 5211, \"to\": 5228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Attention on other goals seemed to act as a sort of buffer against the stress of elite sport, Lavallee said.\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5338, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Attention\", \"from\": 5230, \"to\": 5239}, {\"ngram\": \"other goals\", \"from\": 5243, \"to\": 5254}, {\"ngram\": \"a sort\", \"from\": 5272, \"to\": 5278}, {\"ngram\": \"buffer\", \"from\": 5282, \"to\": 5288}, {\"ngram\": \"the stress\", \"from\": 5297, \"to\": 5307}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sport\", \"from\": 5311, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"Lavallee\", \"from\": 5324, \"to\": 5332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletic success at the elite level will always demandsomedegree of extraordinary focus and discipline.\", \"from\": 5342, \"to\": 5445, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletic success\", \"from\": 5342, \"to\": 5358}, {\"ngram\": \"the elite level\", \"from\": 5362, \"to\": 5377}, {\"ngram\": \"extraordinary focus\", \"from\": 5410, \"to\": 5429}, {\"ngram\": \"discipline\", \"from\": 5434, \"to\": 5444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And adding another set of commitments to a demanding schedule does not magically equal mental health.\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another set\", \"from\": 5457, \"to\": 5468}, {\"ngram\": \"commitments\", \"from\": 5472, \"to\": 5483}, {\"ngram\": \"a demanding schedule\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5507}, {\"ngram\": \"mental health\", \"from\": 5533, \"to\": 5546}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, the tennis star Serena Williams and the track athlete Allyson Felix-who has won more championship and Olympics medals than any other runner in history-have shared at length about balancing motherhood with the demands of elite sport.\", \"from\": 5548, \"to\": 5794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5578, \"end\": 5593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}, {\"begin\": 5616, \"end\": 5623, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Maynard_Gibson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allyson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Maynard_Gibson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allyson_Maynard_Gibson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"instance\", \"from\": 5552, \"to\": 5560}, {\"ngram\": \"the track athlete\", \"from\": 5598, \"to\": 5615}, {\"ngram\": \"more championship and Olympics medals\", \"from\": 5642, \"to\": 5679}, {\"ngram\": \"any other runner\", \"from\": 5685, \"to\": 5701}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5712}, {\"ngram\": \"length\", \"from\": 5728, \"to\": 5734}, {\"ngram\": \"motherhood\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5761}, {\"ngram\": \"the demands\", \"from\": 5767, \"to\": 5778}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sport\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But both are keen to emphasize that an athlete should not be limited to their work in the arena.\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 5831, \"to\": 5841}, {\"ngram\": \"their work\", \"from\": 5867, \"to\": 5877}, {\"ngram\": \"the arena\", \"from\": 5881, \"to\": 5890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the world's highest-profile athletes start foundations, complete an advanced degree, or start a family during their competitive career; Biles's success this week follows a break from her sport, during which she married the NFL player Jonathan Owens and focused on life outside the gym.\", \"from\": 5892, \"to\": 6185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6123, \"end\": 6126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9997712240290216, \"rank\": 0.00022874791440981684, \"text\": \"NFL\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Football_League\"}, {\"begin\": 6134, \"end\": 6148, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"score\": 0.9999928980975966, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jonathan Owens\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jonathan_Owens\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world's highest-profile athletes\", \"from\": 5900, \"to\": 5936}, {\"ngram\": \"foundations\", \"from\": 5943, \"to\": 5954}, {\"ngram\": \"an advanced degree\", \"from\": 5965, \"to\": 5983}, {\"ngram\": \"a family\", \"from\": 5994, \"to\": 6002}, {\"ngram\": \"their competitive career\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6034}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles's success\", \"from\": 6036, \"to\": 6051}, {\"ngram\": \"a break\", \"from\": 6070, \"to\": 6077}, {\"ngram\": \"her sport\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6092}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 6164, \"to\": 6168}, {\"ngram\": \"the gym\", \"from\": 6177, \"to\": 6184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If she decides now to retire permanently, the attention she gave to those other pieces of her life will be the basis of something more.\", \"from\": 6186, \"to\": 6321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the attention\", \"from\": 6228, \"to\": 6241}, {\"ngram\": \"those other pieces\", \"from\": 6254, \"to\": 6272}, {\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6284}, {\"ngram\": \"the basis\", \"from\": 6293, \"to\": 6302}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 6306, \"to\": 6315}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For Schmitt, too, stepping away helped her return to her sport: Following the 2016 Olympics, she retired from swimming and started a master's degree and an internship.\", \"from\": 6325, \"to\": 6492, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Schmitt\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6336}, {\"ngram\": \"her sport\", \"from\": 6378, \"to\": 6387}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Olympics\", \"from\": 6399, \"to\": 6416}, {\"ngram\": \"a master's degree\", \"from\": 6456, \"to\": 6473}, {\"ngram\": \"an internship\", \"from\": 6478, \"to\": 6491}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2018, a nagging sense of unfinished business prompted her to start competing again.\", \"from\": 6493, \"to\": 6579, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a nagging sense\", \"from\": 6502, \"to\": 6517}, {\"ngram\": \"unfinished business\", \"from\": 6521, \"to\": 6540}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even after she put her studies on pause to train for the 2020 Games, she felt more like a whole person than she did before her break from swimming, she told me, and was able to see sports as just one part of a long life stretching out before her.\", \"from\": 6580, \"to\": 6826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her studies\", \"from\": 6599, \"to\": 6610}, {\"ngram\": \"pause\", \"from\": 6614, \"to\": 6619}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Games\", \"from\": 6633, \"to\": 6647}, {\"ngram\": \"a whole person\", \"from\": 6668, \"to\": 6682}, {\"ngram\": \"her break\", \"from\": 6703, \"to\": 6712}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 6718, \"to\": 6726}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 6761, \"to\": 6767}, {\"ngram\": \"just one part\", \"from\": 6771, \"to\": 6784}, {\"ngram\": \"a long life\", \"from\": 6788, \"to\": 6799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She did not quite attain the same heights she had in London, but she won another silver and another bronze before stepping back again from competitive life.\", \"from\": 6827, \"to\": 6983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6880, \"end\": 6886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.1862796219585317e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same heights\", \"from\": 6852, \"to\": 6868}, {\"ngram\": \"another silver\", \"from\": 6900, \"to\": 6914}, {\"ngram\": \"another bronze\", \"from\": 6919, \"to\": 6933}, {\"ngram\": \"competitive life\", \"from\": 6966, \"to\": 6982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This type of thinking can help athletes move past moments in competition that they can not control.\", \"from\": 6987, \"to\": 7086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This type\", \"from\": 6987, \"to\": 6996}, {\"ngram\": \"thinking\", \"from\": 7000, \"to\": 7008}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 7018, \"to\": 7026}, {\"ngram\": \"moments\", \"from\": 7037, \"to\": 7044}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 7048, \"to\": 7059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sometimes your very best, usually worthy of gold, is not enough-or there is an unexpected slip, or someone else just does better.\", \"from\": 7087, \"to\": 7216, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 7131, \"to\": 7135}, {\"ngram\": \"an unexpected slip\", \"from\": 7163, \"to\": 7181}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 7186, \"to\": 7193}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When, at 37, Stefanie Reid competed in the long-jump event at the 2021 Tokyo Paralympics, she achieved, in her words, the best performance of her life.\", \"from\": 7217, \"to\": 7368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7230, \"end\": 7243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanie_Reid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanie Reid\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanie_Reid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanie_Reid\"}, {\"begin\": 7288, \"end\": 7293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6247511041848413, \"rank\": 0.6006373709392331, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the long-jump event\", \"from\": 7256, \"to\": 7275}, {\"ngram\": \"her words\", \"from\": 7324, \"to\": 7333}, {\"ngram\": \"the best performance\", \"from\": 7335, \"to\": 7355}, {\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 7359, \"to\": 7367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet she came in fourth, three centimeters away from a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 7369, \"to\": 7436, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bronze medal\", \"from\": 7421, \"to\": 7435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was so hard finishing like that: so much joy and so muchCould you not have just squeezed your glutes together just a little bit longer and sailed a bit farther?\\\"\", \"from\": 7437, \"to\": 7602, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"so much joy\", \"from\": 7474, \"to\": 7485}, {\"ngram\": \"your glutes\", \"from\": 7530, \"to\": 7541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"she told me.\", \"from\": 7603, \"to\": 7615, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But after a disastrous injury in 2019, just being at the Games seemed like a miracle, and to jump the farthest she ever had at a Paralympic Games gave her as much satisfaction as when she'd won the silver in the same event in 2012.\", \"from\": 7616, \"to\": 7847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a disastrous injury\", \"from\": 7626, \"to\": 7645}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 7669, \"to\": 7678}, {\"ngram\": \"a miracle\", \"from\": 7691, \"to\": 7700}, {\"ngram\": \"a Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 7743, \"to\": 7761}, {\"ngram\": \"as much satisfaction\", \"from\": 7771, \"to\": 7791}, {\"ngram\": \"the silver\", \"from\": 7810, \"to\": 7820}, {\"ngram\": \"the same event\", \"from\": 7824, \"to\": 7838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"C\\u00e9line Kosirnik, a sport-and-performance psychologist and researcher at the University of Lausanne, would call Reid's outlook self-compassion.\", \"from\": 7851, \"to\": 7993, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"C\\u00e9line Kosirnik\", \"from\": 7851, \"to\": 7866}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport-and-performance psychologist\", \"from\": 7868, \"to\": 7904}, {\"ngram\": \"researcher\", \"from\": 7909, \"to\": 7919}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 7923, \"to\": 7937}, {\"ngram\": \"Lausanne\", \"from\": 7941, \"to\": 7949}, {\"ngram\": \"Reid's outlook self-compassion\", \"from\": 7962, \"to\": 7992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We talk a lot in the sport world about mental toughness, and how you need to be strong, and you need to always surpass yourself, et cetera, and I agree: It is a world of performance.\", \"from\": 7994, \"to\": 8177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the sport world\", \"from\": 8012, \"to\": 8027}, {\"ngram\": \"mental toughness\", \"from\": 8034, \"to\": 8050}, {\"ngram\": \"et cetera\", \"from\": 8124, \"to\": 8133}, {\"ngram\": \"a world\", \"from\": 8154, \"to\": 8161}, {\"ngram\": \"performance\", \"from\": 8165, \"to\": 8176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But we also need to learn to give ourselves kindness and support when we need it,\\\" she told me.\", \"from\": 8178, \"to\": 8273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"kindness\", \"from\": 8222, \"to\": 8230}, {\"ngram\": \"support\", \"from\": 8235, \"to\": 8242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Schmitt, too, has a tactic for this: Every time she walks through a doorway, she says a positive affirmation about herself.\", \"from\": 8277, \"to\": 8400, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Schmitt\", \"from\": 8277, \"to\": 8284}, {\"ngram\": \"a tactic\", \"from\": 8295, \"to\": 8303}, {\"ngram\": \"a doorway\", \"from\": 8343, \"to\": 8352}, {\"ngram\": \"a positive affirmation\", \"from\": 8363, \"to\": 8385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One: You do not realize how many doors you go through every day,\\\" she told me, laughing.\", \"from\": 8401, \"to\": 8490, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"how many doors\", \"from\": 8426, \"to\": 8440}, {\"ngram\": \"every day\", \"from\": 8456, \"to\": 8465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes you stop under the door, and you are like:What can I say that's positive about myself?It just helps you reframe that thinking and think of yourself more in a positive light.\\\"\", \"from\": 8491, \"to\": 8676, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the door\", \"from\": 8517, \"to\": 8525}, {\"ngram\": \"that thinking\", \"from\": 8614, \"to\": 8627}, {\"ngram\": \"a positive light\", \"from\": 8658, \"to\": 8674}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This type of thinking, Kosirnik said, can give athletes a competitive advantage.\", \"from\": 8680, \"to\": 8760, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This type\", \"from\": 8680, \"to\": 8689}, {\"ngram\": \"thinking\", \"from\": 8693, \"to\": 8701}, {\"ngram\": \"Kosirnik\", \"from\": 8703, \"to\": 8711}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 8727, \"to\": 8735}, {\"ngram\": \"a competitive advantage\", \"from\": 8736, \"to\": 8759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not even the best of the best win every time: In her final two events of this Olympics, balance beam and floor, Biles came in fifth and third, respectively.\", \"from\": 8761, \"to\": 8917, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best win\", \"from\": 8782, \"to\": 8794}, {\"ngram\": \"her final two events\", \"from\": 8810, \"to\": 8830}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympics\", \"from\": 8834, \"to\": 8847}, {\"ngram\": \"balance beam\", \"from\": 8849, \"to\": 8861}, {\"ngram\": \"floor\", \"from\": 8866, \"to\": 8871}, {\"ngram\": \"Biles\", \"from\": 8873, \"to\": 8878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Without self-compassion, athletes can spiral.\", \"from\": 8918, \"to\": 8963, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"self-compassion\", \"from\": 8926, \"to\": 8941}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 8943, \"to\": 8951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They might lose sleep, or fail to properly fuel themselves.\", \"from\": 8964, \"to\": 9023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sleep\", \"from\": 8980, \"to\": 8985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their mental health deteriorates, and in training or at the next competition, their performance is negatively affected.\", \"from\": 9024, \"to\": 9143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their mental health\", \"from\": 9024, \"to\": 9043}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 9065, \"to\": 9073}, {\"ngram\": \"the next competition\", \"from\": 9080, \"to\": 9100}, {\"ngram\": \"their performance\", \"from\": 9102, \"to\": 9119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee has unveiled a framework to help athletes prepare for life after competition; still, every person I spoke with for this story brought up the need for more mental-health support for athletes, whether it's offered by teams, sports federations, or independent organizations.\", \"from\": 9144, \"to\": 9451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9148, \"end\": 9179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a framework\", \"from\": 9193, \"to\": 9204}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 9213, \"to\": 9221}, {\"ngram\": \"life\", \"from\": 9234, \"to\": 9238}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 9245, \"to\": 9256}, {\"ngram\": \"every person\", \"from\": 9265, \"to\": 9277}, {\"ngram\": \"this story\", \"from\": 9295, \"to\": 9305}, {\"ngram\": \"the need\", \"from\": 9317, \"to\": 9325}, {\"ngram\": \"more mental-health support\", \"from\": 9330, \"to\": 9356}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 9361, \"to\": 9369}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 9395, \"to\": 9400}, {\"ngram\": \"sports federations\", \"from\": 9402, \"to\": 9420}, {\"ngram\": \"independent organizations\", \"from\": 9425, \"to\": 9450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until such support manifests, talking about these problems is the best tool that athletes have.\", \"from\": 9452, \"to\": 9547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"such support manifests\", \"from\": 9458, \"to\": 9480}, {\"ngram\": \"these problems\", \"from\": 9496, \"to\": 9510}, {\"ngram\": \"the best tool\", \"from\": 9514, \"to\": 9527}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 9533, \"to\": 9541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group.\", \"from\": 9553, \"to\": 9601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9578, \"end\": 9594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlantic Monthly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 9602, \"to\": 9622, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply\", \"from\": 9624, \"to\": 9712, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This site\", \"from\": 9624, \"to\": 9633}, {\"ngram\": \"reCAPTCHA\", \"from\": 9650, \"to\": 9659}, {\"ngram\": \"the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms\", \"from\": 9664, \"to\": 9696}, {\"ngram\": \"Serviceapply\", \"from\": 9700, \"to\": 9712}]}]}"